From: Nick <nick@local>
Subject: [PATCH] media: jaguar2: fix multi-stream VC capture

The NVP6324 MIPI TX arbiter needs one reset bounce after initialization
to properly synchronize all 4 virtual channels. Without this, VC1-VC3
only deliver frames intermittently (~3fps instead of full rate).

However, the plug_state_check_work repeatedly bounces the arbiter
whenever it detects hot-plug status changes. During active multi-stream
capture, these repeated bounces momentarily kill all MIPI TX output,
causing the CIF to lose sync and freeze.

Fix: allow exactly ONE arbiter bounce after stream start (using the
is_reset field as a bounce counter), then suppress all subsequent
bounces during streaming. This provides the needed post-init sync
while preventing disruptive repeated bounces during capture.

---
 drivers/media/i2c/jaguar2_drv/jaguar2_v4l2.c | 12 +++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/i2c/jaguar2_drv/jaguar2_v4l2.c b/drivers/media/i2c/jaguar2_drv/jaguar2_v4l2.c
--- a/drivers/media/i2c/jaguar2_drv/jaguar2_v4l2.c
+++ b/drivers/media/i2c/jaguar2_drv/jaguar2_v4l2.c
@@ -704,7 +704,17 @@
 	if (jaguar2->hot_plug)
 		dev_info(&client->dev, "%s has plug motion? (%s)", __func__,
 				jaguar2->hot_plug ? "true" : "false");
-	if (jaguar2->hot_plug) {
+	/*
+	 * Allow one arbiter bounce after stream start to synchronize all
+	 * VCs, then suppress subsequent bounces during active streaming
+	 * to prevent MIPI TX disruption that freezes CIF channels.
+	 * is_reset is cleared to 0 at stream start; we use it as a
+	 * bounce counter.
+	 */
+	if (jaguar2->hot_plug && jaguar2->streaming && jaguar2->is_reset > 0) {
+		dev_info(&client->dev, "skipping arbiter bounce (streaming, already synced)");
+	} else if (jaguar2->hot_plug) {
+		jaguar2->is_reset = 1;
 		dev_dbg(&client->dev, "queue_delayed_work 1500ms, if has hot plug motion.");
 		queue_delayed_work(jaguar2->plug_state_check.state_check_wq,
 				   &jaguar2->plug_state_check.d_work, msecs_to_jiffies(1500));
